parameters:
\nc<>Kei-san, was it? You mentioned earlier that you wanted to
hear a detailed explanation about the Paradise Cult, right?

\nc<>I see. I was thinking about it after hearing your story the
other day. It's definitely wrong to deny something without
knowing about it.

\nc<>Actually, this is Kei-san's first time coming here, so I'm a
bit nervous... B-but I'll do my best to explain!

\nc<>(...Well, actually, I came here to gather information about
Villan.)
\nc<>(That bald-headed Villan himself wasn't that strong.)

\nc<>(If we defeat the subordinates, we should be able to gain
complete control.)

\nc<>You mentioned the Paradise Cult, right? What kind of
religion do they believe in? There are various types of
gods, aren't there?

\nc<>Y-Yes, that's right. First of all, we are classified as a
religious organization, but what we believe in is not a
specific god, but the existence of paradise itself.

\nc<>Yes! It's a place where people truly connect with each other
and everyone becomes happy. It's a place where an impossible
ideal becomes a reality!

\nc<>Ah, you thought it was like a fake religion, right? Well, I
thought the same at first too.
\nc<>If you think about it, it's actually something normal.

\nc<>See, it's only natural to make an effort to get along with
others and be happy in society, right?
\nc<>This place just makes it a little more clear.

\nc<>(Trying to cover it up like that just makes it seem even
more like a fake religion...)
\nc<>(I shouldn't say things like that. Yeah.)

\nc<>Seeing is believing, they say. So, um, I will guide you,
so please see and feel for yourself what the Paradise
Religion is like.
